    "description": "<p>Clerics can reach out and call upon the power of a deity to aid them in battle and to support them and their allies. Clerics can range from a knowledgeable priest, to a knight in holy armor. They reach out to their deity to empower their magic in ways mortals normally can not.</p><p><em><strong>Source of Power:</strong></em> Clerics have a relationship with a powerful deity, or deities, that they are in service to. Through their faith, they’re granted magical power by their deity. They could serve a good god of life that grants them healing magic, or an evil god of death that grants them abilities to end life.</p><p> </p><h2>Starting Equipment</h2><ul><li>2 Light Weapons or 1 Light Weapon and a Light Shield (or Heavy Weapon / Heavy Shield if you choose the Protector Holy Order, see below)</li><li>1 set of Novice Light Armor (or Heavy Armor if you choose the Protector Holy Order, see below)</li><li>X or Y “Packs” (Adventuring Packs Coming Soon)</li></ul><p> </p><h2>Cleric Spellcasting Mastery</h2><p><strong>Combat Masteries: </strong>Light Weapons, Light Armor, Light Shields, Spellcasting.</p><p><strong>Spell List: </strong>When you learn a new Spell, you can choose any Spell on the Divine Spell List.</p><p><strong>Alpha Note: </strong>You get access to the “Premade List” of Holy & Restoration. This is the only Premade List that you have to choose from until the Spell List Alpha Update.</p><p><strong>Cantrips Known: </strong>You learn a number of Spells with the Cantrip Spell Tag as shown in the Cantrips Known column of the Class Table.</p><p><strong>Spells Known:</strong> You learn an additional number of Spells (with or without the Cantrip Spell Tag) as shown in the Spells Known column of the Class Table.</p><p><strong>Mana Points:</strong> You have a maximum number of Mana Points equal to your Prime. Additionally, your maximum increases by an amount as shown in the Mana Points column of the Class Table.</p><p> </p><h2>Class Table</h2><table 